metadata.name: The Norse Goddess Freyja
metadata.description: The breathtaking Freyja is from the realm of Vanaheimr, home of the Vanir gods. She is known by many names Valfreyja, Vanadis, Mard√∂ll and Gef. She chooses first of the slain warriors, she taught Odin his magic, goddess of love, beauty and war. She is a shapeshifter, skilled practitioner of magic and mysteries of the runes. To gaze upon her is the sight of true beauty and power. Her wisdom, grace and knowledge are incomparable. Words cannot truly describe her, This is Freyja.
